        <div class="cell medium-16 columns pbxl flex-container auto mrn margin-auto">
          <article class="full">
            <header class="entry-header">
              <h2>Appeal a zoning decision to the Zoning Board of Adjustment (ZBA)</h2>
            </header>
            <div id="service-default" data-swiftype-index='true' data-swiftype-name="body" data-swiftype-type="text" class="entry-content">
                <div class="row">
	<div class="columns">
		<p>If the <a href="https://www.phila.gov/departments/department-of-licenses-and-inspections/">Department of Licenses and Inspections</a> (L&amp;I) refuses your zoning/use registration application, you have 30 days to appeal to the Zoning Board of Adjustment (ZBA). L&amp;I may also refer your case to ZBA. ZBA will consider whether to grant you a variance or special exception. These decisions will allow you to continue with your plans.</p>
	</div>
</div>        
  <div class="grid-x">
    <div class="cell">
      <section>
                                              <h3 class="black bg-ghost-gray phm-mu mbm" id="who">Who</h3>
                      <div class="phm-mu">
                
                  <p>You can appeal to the ZBA if:</p>
<ul>
<li>Your application for zoning/use registration permit has been refused.</li>
<li>Your case has been referred to ZBA for consideration of a special exception.</li>
<li>You wish to appeal a permit issued or any decision by L&amp;I.</li>
</ul>
 

          
          
                      </div>

      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-x">
    <div class="cell">
      <section>
                                              <h3 class="black bg-ghost-gray phm-mu mbm" id="requirements">Requirements</h3>
                      <div class="phm-mu">
                
                  <p>Carefully follow the <a href="https://www.phila.gov/documents/zoning-board-of-adjustment-appeal-materials/">instructions</a> ZBA provides or your hearing will be postponed.</p>
<p>Determine if you need an attorney. Attorney requirements vary, depending on who is being represented.</p>
<ul>
<li>An individual may appear before the ZBA in person or be represented by an attorney authorized to practice in Pennsylvania.</li>
<li>A corporation, including nonprofit corporations and LLCs, must be represented by an attorney authorized to practice in Pennsylvania.</li>
<li>A partnership may appear before the ZBA by one of its partners with written authorization from the general or managing partner or by an attorney authorized to practice in Pennsylvania.</li>
</ul>
 

          
          
                      </div>

      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-x">
    <div class="cell">
      <section>
                                              <h3 class="black bg-ghost-gray phm-mu mbm" id="cost">Cost</h3>
                      <div class="phm-mu">
                
                  <p>You must pay a filing fee to appeal to the ZBA. The filing fee will be listed on your refusal or referral issued by L&amp;I.</p>
<p>The fee to appeal varies by property:</p>
<ul>
<li>Existing one-or-two-family dwellings — $125</li>
<li>New one-or-two-family dwellings — $300</li>
<li>All other properties — $300</li>
<li>Administrative review — $200</li>
<li>Reposting of notices — $65</li>
<li>Accelerated hearing — $750 per property (maximum of $2250)</li>
</ul>
 

          
          
                      </div>

      </section>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-x">
    <div class="cell">
      <section>
                                              <h3 class="black bg-ghost-gray phm-mu mbm" id="how">How</h3>
                      <div class="phm-mu">
                
                  <p>ZBA will schedule your case for a hearing. At that hearing you will be able to testify as to why ZBA should grant the variance or special exception, or overturn the L&amp;I decision. Anyone who wishes to testify regarding your case will be allowed to do so.</p>
<p>If ZBA denies your request, you have 30 days to appeal that decision to the Court of Common Pleas.</p>
<h4>Required materials</h4>
<p>A complete application package includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>An application for <a title="https://www.phila.gov/media/20200211132826/Application-for-Appeal-3.28.18.pdf" href="https://www.phila.gov/media/20200211132826/Application-for-Appeal-3.28.18.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-auth="NotApplicable">appeal</a> or <a title="https://www.phila.gov/media/20190318162455/Application-for-Special-Exception-81-49-A.pdf" href="https://www.phila.gov/media/20190318162455/Application-for-Special-Exception-81-49-A.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" data-auth="NotApplicable">special exception</a>.</li>
<li>A printed copy of the <a href="https://forms.phila.gov/form/project-information-form/">Project Information Form</a>.</li>
<li>One signed copy of the Notice of Refusal or Referral (or a copy of the decision rendered by L&amp;I).</li>
<li>Your filing fee.</li>
</ul>
<h4>By mail or in person</h4>
<p>To file a paper application, you can mail in the required materials or deliver them in person.</p>
<p>Appointments are required for filing an appeal in person. You can use our <a class="external" href="https://kiosk.us2.qless.com/kiosk/app/home/7100000030">online appointment system</a> to schedule your visit. Once you’ve entered your contact information, select “Zoning Board of Adjustment” and choose “File appeal.”</p>
<p>Zoning Board of Adjustment<br />
1515 Arch St., 18th Floor, Room 18-006<br />
Philadelphia, PA 19102<br />
(215) 686-2429, 2430</p>
<h4>Online</h4>
<p>If you receive a refusal in eCLIPSE, you may file your appeal online. Upload a PDF copy of the completed application package and pay in eCLIPSE.</p>
<p>You must upload all of the required documents with your application. Incomplete applications will not be processed.</p>
 

          
          
                      </div>

      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
  

<!-- Additional Content-->
</div>
<section>
    <div class="row">
    <div class="columns">
      <section>
        <h3 class="black bg-ghost-gray phm-mu mtl mbm">Forms & instructions</h3>
                  <div class="phm-mu">
                          <div>
                <a href="https://www.phila.gov/documents/zoning-board-of-adjustment-appeal-materials/"><i class="far fa-file-alt fa-fw" aria-hidden="true"></i>Zoning Board of Adjustment (ZBA) appeals materials</a>
              </div>
                                    </section>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  
  <div class="row equal-height mtl">
        <div class="medium-24 columns">
        <div class="panel info equal">
          <aside>
            <h3><i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i> Did you know?</h3>
            <p>You can review zoning appeal files at the ZBA office. To schedule your visit, use our <a class="external" href="https://kiosk.us2.qless.com/kiosk/app/home/7100000030">online appointment system</a>. Once you&#8217;ve entered your contact information, select &#8220;Zoning Board of Adjustment&#8221; and choose &#8220;File review.&#8221;</p>
          </aside>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    </div>
</section>
